            <div class="panel panel-default">
                <!-- Accordion Heading -->
                <div class="panel-heading container-clipboard">
                    <div class="panel-title">
                        <a id="accordion-1526417205045-our-community--our-responsibility--addressing-sexual-violence-at-ryerson-from-policy-to-supports" role="tab" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#" href="#accordion-content-1526417205045-our-community--our-responsibility--addressing-sexual-violence-at-ryerson-from-policy-to-supports" aria-controls="accordion-content-1526417205045-our-community--our-responsibility--addressing-sexual-violence-at-ryerson-from-policy-to-supports" aria-expanded="false">
                            Our Community, Our Responsibility: Addressing Sexual Violence at Ryerson from Policy to Supports
                        </a>
                    </div>
                    
                </div>
                <!-- Accordion Body -->
                <div tabindex="0" id="accordion-content-1526417205045-our-community--our-responsibility--addressing-sexual-violence-at-ryerson-from-policy-to-supports" class="panel-collapse collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="accordion-1526417205045-our-community--our-responsibility--addressing-sexual-violence-at-ryerson-from-policy-to-supports">
                    <div class="panel-body ">
                        <div class="1526417205045 stackparsys">










				
				<div class="resText parbase section">


























<div class="res-text richtextContent background-hidden" id="4f214887-fd73-479e-9e76-65ef293495f5" >

    <p>This workshop is designed to help Ryerson community members become knowledgeable on how to build consent culture on campus, including; Ryerson’s commitment to supporting those affected bys sexual violence as outlined in the policy; consent as an everyday practice, sexual violence and impacts of trauma; sexual harassment in the workplace; how to deal with disclosures and make referrals to supports on and off campus. </p>
    





</div>
<script>$(document).ready(function(){addCoursePopover("#4f214887-fd73-479e-9e76-65ef293495f5");});</script></div>

				</div>

                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="panel panel-default">
                <!-- Accordion Heading -->
                <div class="panel-heading container-clipboard">
                    <div class="panel-title">
                        <a id="accordion-1526417209609-be-brave--dealing-with-disclosures-and-reporting-sexual-violence" role="tab" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#" href="#accordion-content-1526417209609-be-brave--dealing-with-disclosures-and-reporting-sexual-violence" aria-controls="accordion-content-1526417209609-be-brave--dealing-with-disclosures-and-reporting-sexual-violence" aria-expanded="false">
                            Be BRAVE: Dealing with Disclosures and Reporting Sexual Violence
                        </a>
                    </div>
                    
                </div>
                <!-- Accordion Body -->
                <div tabindex="0" id="accordion-content-1526417209609-be-brave--dealing-with-disclosures-and-reporting-sexual-violence" class="panel-collapse collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="accordion-1526417209609-be-brave--dealing-with-disclosures-and-reporting-sexual-violence">
                    <div class="panel-body ">
                        <div class="1526417209609 stackparsys">










				
				<div class="resText parbase section">


























<div class="res-text richtextContent background-hidden" id="3c17d883-0463-4c92-a8ed-870fa0cd6041" >

    <p>Begin by listening, respect confidentiality, ask what they need, validate and empathize are the first steps to dealing with disclosures of sexual violence. In this training, participants will learn the difference between disclosure and reporting and how to support someone affected by sexual violence. In addition participants will learn how to refer them to supports on and off campus and how to practice self-care after trauma exposure. </p>
    





</div>
<script>$(document).ready(function(){addCoursePopover("#3c17d883-0463-4c92-a8ed-870fa0cd6041");});</script></div>

